last stop.tips: You want your middle lane brawler to help pinch or scout out (Vision gear) other lanes. Games usually depend on who can push up their left side the best to establish map control.
last stop.s31 tips: Prioritize a good sniper as gem carrier in middle. In bushes you can run an anti agro, assassin, or brawler good at scouting.

triple dribble.tips: Map is symmetrical now with unbreakable walls in the middle compared to last season. Throwers are more toxic on this map, so make sure you have brawlers that can tank their shots or move past walls to get to them. Like other Brawl Ball maps make sure you still have DPS to deal with tanks as well.
triple dribble.s31 tips: Thrower heavy draft. If you're not going a thrower or thrower counter pick brawlers that are tanky enough to shrug off some damage to create space, fast enough to close distance against throwers, or good wall peakers.

bridge too far.tips: DO NOT GO KIT. Chuck is a chaotic pick as it forces both sides to only draft base race DPS brawlers. If Chuck is banned then it becomes a long range control game with high DPS long range or high mobility brawlers. First pick is stronger than last pick here.
bridge too far.s31 tips: Long range and water brawlers good. Make sure you have at least one serious damage dealer on the safe that can't be ignored.

shooting star.tips: Long range skill based interactions. You usually want to run snipers on either side, then a thrower or someone who can deal with a thrower in the middle. Make sure you don't have three of the same type of brawler.
shooting star.s31 tips: Run snipers. If enemy has a thrower make sure you have a long range assassin or your own thrower.

ring of fire.tips: Two brawlers rush middle, other brawler pushes into enemy grass to spawn camp. If enemy is sneaking into your grass one of the zone brawlers should stay back to keep them out. Make sure that your brawler in the middle is tanky enough to stay on zone.
ring of fire.s31 tips: Two people down middle, then another person preventing enemy from spawn camping in grass

belles rock.tips: Go for only one or two snipers and a thrower. Snipers aren't as good as you think since throwers and Rico can easily shut down lanes.
belles rock.s31 tips: Late pick is very strong as throwers or assassins so be careful of those.

out in the open.tips: Vision gear good to scout people and push them into their spawn. Your comp should have anti agro, a meta sniper objectively better than the other ones, then a generalist sniper to add pressure. Look out for Nani or Darryl last picks.
out in the open.s31 tips: Everyone will probably run a sniper. Assassins are a good last pick so make sure you have a mid range anti agro to create space against snipers or counter assassins.

pinball dreams.tips: Last pick tanks or throwers are very dangerous. Make sure to have DPS, wall break, and tanks in your team to be able to handle anything.
pinball dreams.s31 tips: Throwers and wall breakers are really strong first picks. Later in draft go for damage dealers or assassins when you know it's safer.

double swoosh.tips: Vision gear > Speed gear for most brawlers on this map. Map is very versatile with what you can run in the middle, leading to a diverse set of last picks as well.
double swoosh.s31 tips: Sneaky map, don't get caught lacking by being cautious with scouting and vision gear.

hideout.tips: First/middle pick generalists that are hard to counter. Last pick assassins or throwers that can counter snipers. Look out for late pick Kit cheese.
hideout.s31 tips: Run snipers unless you're playing against pros. Other good classes are assassins (Mortis) and long range supports (8-Bit, R-T).

center stage.tips: Safe first picks are DPS or support brawlers with Vision gear to scout out enemies and control bushes. Tanks are solid for pushing up the map and making goals. Sixth pick is the most dangerous here as throwers can be picked for teams with too much DPS or tank counters/strong tanks to counter a heavy tank team.
center stage.s31 tips: Team comp should have a bush scouter and tank counter.

safe zone.tips: Defensive start while people build up supers, sneak up through middle or side. Don't worry about late picks and try to fit as much DPS against the safe as possible.
safe zone.s31 tips: 6th pick can make some dirty comps, beware double throwers if you have snipers and no throwers. Consider breaking open map and using snipers if enemy has only midrange brawlers.

pit stop.tips: Complete base race. 1 defender + 2 rush. Angelo not good until high elo

dueling beetles.tips: Spen is just talking about brawlers that do well here. Just know that there are a lot of brawlers that are good at abusing the unbreakable walls here or holding the zone with pressure. Lookout for cheese with Berry and a tank.
dueling beetles.s31 tips: Larry & Lawrie and Barley as best throwers plus whatever newest brawlers in game are for first pick. Run assassins, tanks, and tank counters later in draft.

split.tips: Two down right, 1 down left. Don't break open right unless thrower, break open left.

canal grande.tips: Control at least one lane, even if it means having three brawlers on one side, to prevent getting spawn trapped. Brawlers that can float on water (Juju and Angelo > Eve) and throwers are generally better than snipers here.
canal grande.s31 tips: Take over middle grass and have brawlers to cover multiple niches (throwers and tanks). Brawlers with artillery capabilities (Penny, Squeak) can also be used.

sneaky fields.tips: Abuse Vision gear on brawlers that aren't tanks. Use aggressive brawlers early on in draft, then pick tank counters or other good scouting brawlers later on in draft

hard rock mine.tips: Tough map to draft. Don't let enemy team get Rico, make sure someone in team has Vision gear or can keep eyes out for someone sneaking into your side of the map.
hard rock mine.s31 tips: Focus on getting a good lane brawler (Surge, Rico, Ruffs, etc) as there are a lot of good middle map brawlers.

kaboom canyon.tips: If you're going to use snipers, send them for the end of the draft to counter the DPS people rush for early on in the draft otherwise they can get overwhelmed. Don't worry too much about last pick.
kaboom canyon.s31 tips: More snipers compared to other Heist maps, make sure you run a brawler that can burst safe for pressure.

hot potato.tips: BASE RACE. Lots of tanks and aggressive brawlers so anti tanks will serve quite well. First and last pick throwers can work on this map, so make sure you have some tankier brawlers in your composition as well. As long as you can keep up the pressure up, you will probably win so you can even get away with having a lot of tanks.
hot potato.s31 tips: BASE RACE, run tanks/throwers that can burst down safe or damage dealers that the tanks will eventually feed.

parallel plays.tips: One defensive left lane with an anti tank or thrower that you need to hold down first, one offensive right lane with an assassin or tank, then a versatile middle area to clean up messes or help secure interactions.
parallel plays.s31 tips: Focus on defensive left lane with a high DPS mid to long range. Middle area will be a versatile long range, then right lane should have an assassin or other aggressive brawler.

open business.tips: Have a balanced team, some sort of DPS/control against tanks, someone to deal with squishy lane brawlers such as a thrower or assassin, then a tanky brawler to hold zone time.
open business.s31 tips: Throwers strong. Options are just a cycle of throwers, wall breakers, tanks/assassins, and anti agro

goldarm gulch.tips: Sniper heavy map, first pick make sure you have someone good at confirming kills or dealing with aggression from enemies later in draft. Brawlers good at playing defensively like Tick and Pearl are good, as well as wall break. Look out for Darryl last pick.
goldarm gulch.s31 tips: Lock in a thrower, most snipers are versatile enough to deal with assassins, then pick an assassin yourself or brawler good when gas closes.

flaring phoenix.tips: Thrower down left, then make sure to have a brawler on the right to prevent thrower from pushing too far into your side. Don't get impatient and overextend, you can usually just wait for gas to close in.
flaring phoenix.s31 tips: Run a thrower and sniper, then a brawler with good synergy or as an enemy counter.

acute angle.tips: Good mid can setup spawn trap

undermine.tips: Spawn trap heavy map, make sure you can control the grass on at least one side of the map. Prioritize DPS or tanks to win lane battles, there are a variety of support you can use in the middle to help pinch lanes.
undermine.s31 tips: Get a sniper in mid and then anti agro, assassin, scout brawler, or wall peaker in bushes. If skill issue in bushes double up in mid(do not triple stack) for more pressure or pinching

penalty kick.s31 tips: Throwers are OP (except for Moe and Kenji). Best throwers are Barley and Larry & Lawrie so use them or ban them. Very easy to get away with random nonsense so make sure you have a good tank counter as well.

snake prarie.tips: All about scouting and sneaking around. Top brawlers have gadgets/star powers to provide vision, otherwise use Vision gear on a non tank. To sneak around have a close range brawler with Speed gear. Besides that, make sure your team is close enough that it can be easy to get revenge kills if a teammate gets into a skirmish.
snake prarie.s31 tips: Group up to be able to get revenge kills (not close enough for one enemy to teamwipe though). Make sure you have brawlers that have vision abilities/gear or are a tank.
